1.00	Garrick_Theater_(Chicago)	Garrick Theater (Chicago)	The Schiller Theatre Building was designed by Louis Sullivan and Dankmar Adler of the firm Adler &amp; Sullivan for the German Opera Company. At the time of its construction, it was one among the tallest buildings in Chicago. Its centerpiece was a 1,300-seat theater, which is considered to be one of the greatest collaborations between Adler and Sullivan by architectural historians.	
